# ——————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————
# Contains data about game colors in YAML format.
# Find a guide explaining how to use YAML if you're interested in modding.
# It's easy to understand even if you had no experience with coding or modding before.
# ——————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————
#                                                  Color structure
# ——————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————
# The left part is the color's name. These names are used in numerous game files like database/league.db.
# The right part is the color's value which can be a hex code or a keyword (bold, underline, etc).
# ——————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————
#                                                   Color creation
# ——————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————
# In order to create a new color, type the desired name followed by a colon and the color's hex code in quotes. Example:
# usomecolor: '#ff6900'
# ——————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————
#                                                   Color prefixes
# ——————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————
# As you may have noticed, some colors have prefixes like u-, l-, d- and others.
# These prefixes are used to indicate color properties:
# 1. u- is used for any normal, "usual" color. For example, ublue is just blue.
# 2. l- is used to indicate that the color is lighter than the usual color. For example, lblue is light blue.
# 3. d- is used to indicate that the color is darker than the usual color. For example, dblue is dark blue.
# 4. g-, y- and similar prefixes are used to indicate that the color is close to another color.
#    For example, gyellow is greenish yellow, ygreen is yellowish green.
#    Important note: the prefix is less important than the part after it, so ygreen is closer to ugreen than gyellow is.
# 5. bg- is a special prefix indicating a background color. It can be combined with other prefixes. More about it below.
# ——————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————
#                                            Background colors (advanced)
# ——————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————
# Background colors are used to color the background instead of the text.
# They are automatically generated by the game and have the following format:
# bg{color_name}: 'bg:{color_value}'
# For example:
# bgsomecolor: 'bg:#ff6900'
#
# Sometimes, though, you don't want the game to automatically generate a background color.
# In order to do that add ! to the end of its name like in "uwhite!".
# The color will still be accessible by its normal name (for example, uwhite and not uwhite!).
# This feature is useful if you want the background color to have a different tone compared to the original
# (then you should add a background color manually like I do with bguwhite) or when you don't want the game to
# generate a background color (for example, the background cannot be bold).
# ——————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————
bold!: bold
underline!: underline
reverse!: reverse
lgrey!: default
uwhite!: bold
bguwhite!: 'bg:#ffffff'
ugrey: '#a0a0a0'
ublack!: '#a0a0a0'
bgublack!: 'bg:#000000'
ubrown: '#904000'
lbrown: '#b03050'
dred: '#da0000'
ured: '#ff2020'
rorange: '#d06030'
uorange: '#e08030'
ugold: '#c0a030'
dyellow: '#c0c030'
uyellow: '#d0d000'
gyellow: '#aac020'
ygreen: '#80c030'
dgreen: '#00a000'
ugreen: '#30c030'
cgreen: '#30c070'
gcyan: '#30c0a0'
ucyan: '#40b0d0'
lblue: '#5090ff'
ublue: '#3030ff'
dblue: '#0000e0'
uviolet: '#8000d0'
dmagenta: '#b030b0'
umagenta: '#e060e0'
upink: '#ffa0a0'
